# Phase 2: Containers & Orchestration (Days 21–40)

## Day 21: Introduction to Docker
- **Objective**: Understand containerization fundamentals and install Docker.
- **Tasks**:
  - Install Docker on your machine.
  - Understand concepts: Containers vs Virtual Machines.
  - Run your first container with `docker run hello-world`.
- **Code Examples**:
  ```bash
  docker run hello-world
  ```
- **Resources**:
  - [Docker Documentation](https://docs.docker.com/get-started/)

## Day 22: Docker Images
- **Objective**: Learn about Docker images and how to create your own.
- **Tasks**:
  - Pull an image from Docker Hub.
  - Create a Dockerfile and build an image.
- **Code Examples**:
  ```Dockerfile
  FROM ubuntu:latest
  RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y curl
  ```
  ```bash
  docker build -t my-ubuntu-image .
  ```
- **Resources**:
  - [Creating Docker Images](https://docs.docker.com/get-started/part2/)

## Day 23: Docker Containers
- **Objective**: Manage Docker containers effectively.
- **Tasks**:
  - Learn how to start, stop, and remove containers.
  - Understand container lifecycle and states.
- **Code Examples**:
  ```bash
  docker ps -a  # List containers
  docker start <container_id>
  docker stop <container_id>
  docker rm <container_id>
  ```
- **Resources**:
  - [Managing Containers](https://docs.docker.com/engine/reference/commandline/cli/)

## Day 24: Docker Volumes
- **Objective**: Persist data using Docker volumes.
- **Tasks**:
  - Understand the differences between volumes and bind mounts.
  - Create and manage volumes.
- **Code Examples**:
  ```bash
  docker volume create my-volume
  docker run -d -v my-volume:/data my-ubuntu-image
  ```
- **Resources**:
  - [Persisting Data](https://docs.docker.com/storage/)

## Day 25: Docker Networking
- **Objective**: Connect containers using Docker networking.
- **Tasks**:
  - Learn about bridge and host networks.
  - Create your custom network.
- **Code Examples**:
  ```bash
  docker network create my-network
  docker run -d --network my-network --name my-container my-ubuntu-image
  ```
- **Resources**:
  - [Networking Overview](https://docs.docker.com/network/)

## Day 26: Introduction to Orchestration
- **Objective**: Understand the need for orchestration in containerized applications.
- **Tasks**:
  - Learn the limitations of managing docker containers manually.
- **Resources**:
  - [Why Orchestration?](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/overview/what-is-kubernetes/)

## Day 27: Kubernetes Overview
- **Objective**: Familiarize yourself with Kubernetes architecture and components.
- **Tasks**:
  - Understand Pods, Nodes, and Clusters.
- **Resources**:
  - [Kubernetes Documentation](https://kubernetes.io/docs/home/)

## Day 28: Setting Up Minikube
- **Objective**: Install Minikube and run Kubernetes locally.
- **Tasks**:
  - Install Minikube and kubectl.
  - Start a local cluster.
- **Code Examples**:
  ```bash
  minikube start
  kubectl get nodes
  ```
- **Resources**:
  - [Minikube Installation](https://minikube.sigs.k8s.io/docs/start/)

## Day 29: Deploying Your First Application
- **Objective**: Deploy a sample application on Kubernetes.
- **Tasks**:
  - Create a deployment and expose it.
- **Code Examples**:
  ```bash
  kubectl create deployment nginx --image=nginx
  kubectl expose deployment nginx --type=LoadBalancer --port=80
  ```
- **Resources**:
  - [Deployments on Kubernetes](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/workloads/controllers/deployment/)

## Day 30: Services in Kubernetes
- **Objective**: Understand Kubernetes services and networking.
- **Tasks**:
  - Explore ClusterIP, NodePort, and LoadBalancer services.
- **Resources**:
  - [Kubernetes Services](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/services-networking/service/)

## Day 31: ConfigMaps and Secrets
- **Objective**: Externalize configurations using ConfigMaps and Secrets.
- **Tasks**:
  - Create and use ConfigMaps and Secrets in applications.
- **Code Examples**:
  ```bash
  kubectl create configmap app-config --from-literal=key=value
  kubectl create secret generic app-secret --from-literal=password=secret
  ```
- **Resources**:
  - [ConfigMaps](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/configuration/configmap/)
  - [Secrets](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/configuration/secret/)

## Day 32: Introduction to AWS EKS
- **Objective**: Understand AWS EKS and its advantages.
- **Tasks**:
  - Explore EKS features and pricing.
- **Resources**:
  - [AWS EKS Documentation](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/eks/latest/userguide/what-is-eks.html)

## Day 33: Creating an EKS Cluster
- **Objective**: Set up an EKS cluster via the AWS Management Console.
- **Tasks**:
  - Follow the steps to create a basic EKS cluster.
- **Resources**:
  - [Creating EKS Cluster](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/eks/latest/userguide/create-cluster.html)

## Day 34: Deploying Applications on EKS
- **Objective**: Deploy an application on EKS.
- **Tasks**:
  - Use the `kubectl` command to deploy.
- **Code Examples**:
  ```bash
  kubectl apply -f deployment.yaml
  ```
- **Resources**:
  - [Deploying on EKS](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/eks/latest/userguide/deploying-applications.html)

## Day 35: Scaling Applications in Kubernetes
- **Objective**: Scale Kubernetes applications effectively.
- **Tasks**:
  - Use commands to increase/decrease replicas.
- **Code Examples**:
  ```bash
  kubectl scale deployment nginx --replicas=3
  ```
- **Resources**:
  - [Scaling Applications](https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/run-application/horizontal-pod-autoscale/)

## Day 36: Monitoring Kubernetes
- **Objective**: Monitor and log Kubernetes applications.
- **Tasks**:
  - Explore tools like Prometheus and Grafana.
- **Resources**:
  - [Monitoring Kubernetes](https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/debug/debug-application/)

## Day 37: Resource Management in Kubernetes
- **Objective**: Manage resources for Kubernetes applications.
- **Tasks**:
  - Set requests and limits for CPU and memory.
- **Resources**:
  - [Managing Resources](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/configuration/manage-resources-containers/)

## Day 38: Introduction to Helm
- **Objective**: Use Helm for managing Kubernetes applications.
- **Tasks**:
  - Install Helm and use it to deploy applications.
- **Resources**:
  - [Helm Documentation](https://helm.sh/docs/)

## Day 39: Continuous Integration/Deployment
- **Objective**: Implement CI/CD with Kubernetes.
- **Tasks**:
  - Explore tools like Jenkins and GitLab CI.
- **Resources**:
  - [CI/CD with Kubernetes](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/overview/what-is-kubernetes/#continuous-integration-and-continuous-deployment)

## Day 40: Best Practices & Security
- **Objective**: Understand best practices for security in containers and orchestration.
- **Tasks**:
  - Explore security best practices for Docker and Kubernetes.
- **Resources**:
  - [Kubernetes Security](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/security/overview/)

---

This phase covers fundamental and advanced concepts in containerization and orchestration, preparing you for using Docker and Kubernetes in real-world applications!